definition.value: Quantification of bisecting N-acetyl glucosamine-containing N-glycans of IgG in a biological sample, typically serum
Quantification of fucosylated N-glycans of IgG in a biological sample, typically serum
Quantification of sialylated N-glycans of IgG in a biological sample, typically serum
Quantification of disialylated N-glycans of IgG in a biological sample, typically serum
Quantification of monosialylated N-glycans of IgG in a biological sample, typically serum
Qunatification of the maximum volume of air that an organism can breathe in and out during a specified period of time, often 1 minute.

Quantification of the rate of change in lipoprotein-associated phospholipase A(2) over the course of time, used as an indicator of risk of cardiovascular events, and a target for certain cardiovascular drugs.

Quantification of the accuracy of matching eye velocity to target velocity during sustained pursuit, typically measured using a video-based eye tracker. Abnormalities of this system have been observed in psychiatric disoreders such as aschizophrenia.

Quantification of the rate of change of eye velocity during the first 100ms of pursuit, typically measured using a video-based eye-tracker. Abnormalities of this sysmtem have been observed in psychiatric disorders such as schizophrenia.
Quantification of the amount of weight gained by a woman during pregnancy.
Quantification of the amount of weight gained by a woman during late pregnancy.
Quantification of the amount of weight gained by a woman during early pregnancy.
Quantification of the amount of growth hormone in a sample, typically blood.

label.value: single cell nucleic acid sequencing protocol

definition.value: A protocol describing the processes performed and equipment used to determine the order of nucleotide bases in a nucleic acid sample from a single cell specimen

label.value: tag based single cell RNA sequencing

definition.value: Single cell sequencing process using an approach where only a short fragment (tag) at a defined position in each RNA molecule is sequenced

label.value: full length single cell RNA sequencing

definition.value: Single cell sequencing process using an approach where the full length of each RNA molecule is sequenced
The standard protocol supplied by Illumina for single cell nucleic acid sequencing
The standard protocol supplied by 10x Genomics for single cell nucleic acid sequencing
The standard protocol defined by Macosko et al for isolating and sequencing the nucleic acid material from single cell specimens

The ratio of platelet count to lymphocyte count, quantified in a blood sample. Both neutrophil-to-lymphocyte ratio and platelet-to-lymphocyte ratio have been proposed as biomarkers for the diagnosis or prognostic prediction of disease.

The ratio of neutrophil count to lymphocyte count, quantified in a blood sample. Both neutrophil-to-lymphocyte ratio and platelet-to-lymphocyte ratio have been proposed as biomarkers for the diagnosis or prognostic prediction of disease.
quantification of the ratio of magnesium to creatinine in a sample, typically a urine sample, a proxy measure for Mg2+ homeostasis
quantification of fractional excretion of magnesium based on the calculation of serum and urinary levels of magneiusm and creatinine. Used as a marker of renal tubular function.

label.value: activities of daily living score measurement

definition.value: quantification of ability to perform daily living activities independently. A proxy to assess functional status in the elderly.
quatification of the muscle circumference of the mid arm. A proxy for muscle mass of the arm.
quatification of the muscle circumference of the calf. A proxy for muscle mass of the leg.

label.value: short physical performance battery score measurement

definition.value: quantification of physical performance. A proxy to assess lower extremity function in the elderly.

label.value: sleep apnea measurement during REM sleep

definition.value: A pause in breathing or shallow breaths during REM sleep.

label.value: sleep apnea measurement during non-REM sleep

definition.value: A pause in breathing or shallow breaths during non-REM sleep.
Quantification of the degree to which an individual is dependent on cannabis, for example based on the number of DSM-IV criteria met for cannabis dependence.

Quantification of the amount of tacrolimus in a sample.  Tacrolimus (TAC) is a common immunosuppressive agent that potently inhibits T-cell function and proliferation through inhibition of calcineurin by binding to FKB12.

Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of mepolizumab stimulus. Mepolizumab is a humanized monoclonal antibody used for the treatment of severe eosinophilic asthma.
The characteristics of a person’s colorectal health, assessed for example by colonoscopy.

An immune response to foreign (donor) antigens due to fetomaternal hemorrhage (ie, transplacental passage of fetal erythrocytes) associated with delivery, trauma, spontaneous or induced abortion, ectopic pregnancy, or invasive obstetric procedures.
The quantification of glucagon, a hormone involved in glucose homeostasis.
The quantification of glucose-dependent insulinotropic peptide, an incretin hormone secreted in response to nutrient stimulation that acts to increase insulin secretion.
The quantification of glucagon-like peptide 1, an incretin hormone secreted in response to nutrient stimulation that acts to increase insulin secretion.
The determination of the amount of matrix metalloproteinase 8 present in a sample
Some quantification of the ability to inhibit maladaptive or inappropriate behavior.

label.value: midregional pro atrial natriuretic peptide measurement

definition.value: Quantification of the levels of midregional pro atrial natriuretic peptide.

label.value: B-type natriuretic peptide to N-terminal pro B-type natriuretic peptide ratio

definition.value: Quantification of the ratio of B-type natriuretic levels to N-terminal pro B-type natriuretic peptide levels.
Quatification of dietary potassium intake by measuring 24 hr urinary potassium levels.
A measurement of some protein which is used as a measure of heart failure.
Quantification of some aspect of insulin response, typically measuring insulin levels in the blood following a glucose challenge

label.value: spine bone mineral density change measurement

definition.value: Quantification of a change in mineral density of the spine bones
Quantifiication of some aspect of mood instability.

Quantification of some aspect of impulsivity related to the increased perceived value of immediate gratification as compared to a larger future reward. The more remote the future reward, the lower its perceived present value (the more it is discounted) and the less likely it is to be chosen.
The DNA that is part of the normal chromosomal complement of an organism.

Typically small, circular, intronless, and maternally inherited, mitochondrial DNA (mtDNA) is the multicopy deoxyribonucleic acid genome of mitochondria, intracellular organelles responsible for vital respiratory chain and oxidative phosphorylation reactions in higher eukaryotes. Replicated and transcribed by a separate enzymatic machinery from that of nuclear DNA, mtDNA encodes only a subset of mitochondrial functions.

cDNA or complementary DNA is complementary in sequence to a particular messenger RNA (mRNA). It is synthesized from mRNA in a reverse transcription reaction by reverse transcriptase enzyme. cDNA can be cloned in a vector and introduced into cells to bring about the expression of that particular gene in those cells.
